  "title": "Ramp Lag Under Concentration",
  "concept": "When supply concentrates in one source, alternate suppliers exist but can't scale fast enough when the dominant source fails—the gap between immediate need and ramp-up capacity creates shortages even when total global capacity is sufficient.",
  "interactiveId": "10c48c5a-ca05-4996-b8da-de312ccba862",
  "sourcePieceId": "070caa7e-bde8-4a71-be10-f73479a0f46d",
  "publishedAt": 1778654422529,
  "voiceScore": 89,
  "qualityFlag": "low",
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Ramp Lag Under Concentration</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --gold: #c9a227;\n    --teal: #1a6b62;\n    --red: #dc2626;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 20px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n    min-width: 160px;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--teal);\n    min-width: 140px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 3.5ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .scenario {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n    gap: 20px;\n    margin: 24px 0;\n  }\n  .panel {\n    padding: 16px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 2px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 8px;\n  }\n  .panel-title {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.05em;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    margin-bottom: 12px;\n  }\n  .supplier-row {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 10px;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n  }\n  .supplier-label {\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n    font-weight: 500;\n    min-width: 80px;\n  }\n  .bar-track {\n    flex: 1;\n    height: 24px;\n    background: var(--line);\n    border-radius: 3px;\n    position: relative;\n    overflow: hidden;\n  }\n  .bar-fill {\n    height: 100%;\n    transition: width 200ms ease-out;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: flex-end;\n    padding-right: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: #fff;\n  }\n  .bar-fill.dominant {\n    background: var(--teal);\n  }\n  .bar-fill.alternate {\n    background: var(--gold);\n  }\n  .bar-fill.gap {\n    background: var(--red);\n  }\n  .metrics {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);\n    gap: 12px;\n    margin-top: 16px;\n    padding-top: 16px;\n    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);\n  }\n  .metric {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    gap: 4px;\n  }\n  .metric-label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em;\n  }\n  .metric-value {\n    font-size: 1.25rem;\n    font-weight: 700;\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n  }\n  .metric-value.shortage {\n    color: var(--red);\n  }\n  .timeline {\n    margin: 16px 0;\n    padding: 12px;\n    background: #fffbf0;\n    border: 1px solid #e5d9a8;\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  .timeline strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n    line-height: 1.6;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 600px) {\n    .scenario {\n      grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n    }\n    .control label {\n      min-width: 120px;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Drag to shift market share before disruption</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Two suppliers serve global demand. Watch what happens when the dominant one goes offline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"concentration\">Dominant share:</label>\n  <input id=\"concentration\" type=\"range\" min=\"50\" max=\"90\" value=\"50\" step=\"5\" aria-describedby=\"concentration-out\">\n  <output id=\"concentration-out\" for=\"concentration\">50%</output>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"scenario\">\n  <div class=\"panel\">\n    <div class=\"panel-title\">Before disruption</div>\n    <div class=\"supplier-row\">\n      <span class=\"supplier-label\">Source A</span>\n      <div class=\"bar-track\">\n        <div class=\"bar-fill dominant\" id=\"before-a\"><span id=\"before-a-val\">50%</span></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"supplier-row\">\n      <span class=\"supplier-label\">Source B</span>\n      <div class=\"bar-track\">\n        <div class=\"bar-fill alternate\" id=\"before-b\"><span id=\"before-b-val\">50%</span></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"metrics\">\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Demand met</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-value\">100%</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Shortage</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-value\">0%</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"panel\">\n    <div class=\"panel-title\">After disruption (Month 1)</div>\n    <div class=\"supplier-row\">\n      <span class=\"supplier-label\">Source A</span>\n      <div class=\"bar-track\">\n        <div class=\"bar-fill dominant\" style=\"width: 0%; opacity: 0.3;\"><span></span></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"supplier-row\">\n      <span class=\"supplier-label\">Source B</span>\n      <div class=\"bar-track\">\n        <div class=\"bar-fill alternate\" id=\"after-b\"><span id=\"after-b-val\">50%</span></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"supplier-row\">\n      <span class=\"supplier-label\" style=\"color: var(--red);\">Gap</span>\n      <div class=\"bar-track\">\n        <div class=\"bar-fill gap\" id=\"gap-bar\"><span id=\"gap-val\">0%</span></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"metrics\">\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Demand met</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-value\" id=\"met-val\">100%</div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"metric\">\n        <div class=\"metric-label\">Shortage</div>\n        <div class=\"metric-value shortage\" id=\"shortage-val\">0%</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"timeline\" id=\"timeline\">\n  <strong>Ramp timeline:</strong> Source B currently operates at 50% of global demand. Scaling to full capacity takes 18–24 months (new equipment, hiring, regulatory approval). Month 1 shortage reflects the gap between what B produces today and what the market needs now.\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">Split evenly, both sources run at steady state. If Source A fails, Source B covers its current share immediately—but can't instantly double output.</p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var slider = document.getElementById('concentration');\n    var conOut = document.getElementById('concentration-out');\n    \n    var beforeA = document.getElementById('before-a');\n    var beforeAVal = document.getElementById('before-a-val');\n    var beforeB = document.getElementById('before-b');\n    var beforeBVal = document.getElementById('before-b-val');\n    \n    var afterB = document.getElementById('after-b');\n    var afterBVal = document.getElementById('after-b-val');\n    var gapBar = document.getElementById('gap-bar');\n    var gapVal = document.getElementById('gap-val');\n    \n    var metVal = document.getElementById('met-val');\n    var shortageVal = document.getElementById('shortage-val');\n    var timeline = document.getElementById('timeline');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n\n    function update() {\n      var shareA = +slider.value;\n      var shareB = 100 - shareA;\n      \n      conOut.textContent = shareA + '%';\n      \n      // Before disruption: both sources operate at their market share\n      beforeA.style.width = shareA + '%';\n      beforeAVal.textContent = shareA + '%';\n      beforeB.style.width = shareB + '%';\n      beforeBVal.textContent = shareB + '%';\n      \n      // After disruption: Source A offline, Source B still at its pre-disruption capacity\n      // The gap is what Source A was supplying that Source B can't immediately replace\n      var immediateSupply = shareB;\n      var gap = shareA;\n      \n      afterB.style.width = immediateSupply + '%';\n      afterBVal.textContent = immediateSupply + '%';\n      gapBar.style.width = gap + '%';\n      gapVal.textContent = gap + '%';\n      \n      metVal.textContent = immediateSupply + '%';\n      shortageVal.textContent = gap + '%';\n      \n      // Timeline explanation scales with concentration\n      var rampMonths;\n      if (shareA >= 80) {\n        rampMonths = '24–36';\n      } else if (shareA >= 70) {\n        rampMonths = '18–24';\n      } else {\n        rampMonths = '12–18';\n      }\n      \n      timeline.innerHTML = '<strong>Ramp timeline:</strong> Source B currently operates at ' + shareB + '% of global demand. Scaling to 100% takes ' + rampMonths + ' months (new equipment, training, regulatory hurdles). The shortage persists until B completes the ramp.';\n      \n      // Caption updates based on concentration level\n      if (shareA >= 80) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Source A handles most global demand. Source B operates at low volume. If A fails, B supplies ' + shareB + '% immediately—but ramping from ' + shareB + '% to 100% takes years, not weeks. The shortage is structural.';\n      } else if (shareA >= 70) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Source A dominates. Source B maintains ' + shareB + '% capacity. When A goes offline, B can't instantly scale—factories, supply chains, and labor pools take 18+ months to expand. Demand outstrips supply until the ramp completes.';\n      } else if (shareA >= 60) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Source A holds the majority. If A fails, Source B covers ' + shareB + '% right away but needs a year to build out the rest. Concentration creates efficiency in normal times and lag in crises.';\n      } else {\n        caption.textContent = 'Split evenly, both sources run at steady state. If Source A fails, Source B covers its current share immediately—but can't instantly double output. Even at 50/50, ramp lag creates a temporary shortage.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    slider.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
